\subsection{Leveled heading-frame acceleration}

The direction estimator uses inertial acceleration in a leveled frame aligned
with boat heading: $+X$ forward, $+Y$ starboard, and $+Z$ up. The body-frame
specific force is rotated to NED, gravity is restored, and the horizontal
components are projected onto the bow heading and starboard axes. Invalid
attitude or an undefined projected bow heading produces no direction output
rather than a body-frame fallback.
